label: @CHECKACCOUNTCODE
description: This variable provides the checking account code of the current disbursed check in the Corporate Check Wizard.

label: @CHECKAMOUNT
description: This variable provides the amount of the current disbursed check in the Corporate Check Wizard.

label: @CHECKMATCHCATEGORY
description: This variable provides the category of the match of the current disbursed check in the Corporate Check Wizard.

label: @CHECKPAYEELINE1
description: This variable provides the Payee Line 1 field value of the current disbursed check

label: @CHECKPAYEELINE2
description: This variable provides the Payee Line 2 field value of the current disbursed check

label: @CHECKPAYEELINE3
description: This variable provides the Payee Line 3 field value of the current disbursed check

label: @CHECKPAYEELINE4
description: This variable provides the Payee Line 4 field value of the current disbursed check

label: @CHECKPAYEELINE5

label: @CHECKTRANCODE
description:
This variable provides the current transaction code responsible for initiating the Corporate Check Wizard. It allows the specfile to use different logic for different check transaction codes.

For example, in the case of performing a Checks Suppressed (KS) transaction, the check has already been disbursed to the member. An OFAC verification may have been performed at the time of the original disbursal.
